content.summary: Driving w270 at 3:37 on mon. 6/13/16. seen disc in sky, reflected light, then disappeared.

content.detailedDescription: On the 8th of june 2016, i was on my way home from dropping off my son with his grandmother in suffern, ny.  i was between exits 9 and 10 on the new jersey turnpike south when a little after 9 pm i saw 3 orbs of light to the west of me hovering over power lines.  i was convinced they were either landing lights from planes (since newark is north of the turnpike and philadelphia airport south) or lights of an antenna ray but neither explanation worked (i am very familiar with landing lights for planes and these orbs had none).  what surprised me most was that they were completely stationary forming a triangle.  about a minute later, another orb appeared south of the others forming a kind of kite tail to the other three.  there then appeared another light with clear lower landing lights which i am almost certain was a helicopter.  as i continued to drive i eventually lost sight of the objects but was able to take 2 poor photographs of them.
content.summary: Glowing, stationary orbs of light

content.detailedDescription: Heading northbound on main st in taxi, saw bright silvery/chrome object in sky. was size of approx. a small cessna aircraft. i asked taxi to drop me off and continued to observe craft. it was spherical in shape, however; it looked like it had two head lights on it. and the craft did look like it had some type of louvers or sharper areas on it. to make sure it was not the sun reflecting off the object i moved direction to opposite side of object and that's when it's headlights moved and it shot up about 100 ft straight then dead stopped again. it hovered for another minute and then rotated and shot off going south/southeast at a fast rate of speed. i have never seen such an object before. helium balloons do not act in this way and it was too big to be such as that.
content.summary: Unbelievable

content.detailedDescription: I dropped my daughter off for swimming practice at the greenleaf pool at 7:35 and then proceeded up the street to the neighborhood gas station to get a pack of smokes and then returned to the pool parking lot at about 7:42 or so. i parked my car and started to take my walk, that i pre planned on doing, for the duration of my daughters practice. when i reached the end of the parking lot, i crossed the street and walked to the left up e.Greenleaf drive towards tuscanny drive. as i was approaching the stop sign at the end of the street, which sits at the top of a slight hill, light reflecting off of an object in the sky caught my eyes. i stopped in my tracks by the stop sign so i could observe the object. it was, what i believe to be, a metallic object that was orb shaped and highly reflective hovering off in the distance just above a development of town houses and trees off of tuscanny drive. when i was convinced that it was a ufo i proceeded to get my phone off my hip to take a video of the object. i put my phone in video mode, pressed the record button and lifted it to the sky and pointed it at the orb...But upon aiming the phone at the orb, my screen was completely black. so i lowered my camera to check the settings. everything was the way it was suppose to be but my screen was still black. i then checked the lens and everything was fine with that so i turned the phone off and then back on to start the process all over again all while occasionally glancing up to make sure that i didnt loose sight of the orb. once my phone was back on i put it in video mode again and pressed record, but this time i made sure that the screen wasnt black and it was recording before i raised my phone to the sky. once i was sure it was working correctly i looked up while raising the camera but the orb was gone...Or invisible. i stood there for about 5 minutes searching the skies to see if i could locate it again. disappointed upon not finding it, i continued my walk by making a left on tuscanny drive. so excited by what i saw, i called my friend, after making a left onto christophers crossing off of tuscanny, to tell him what i saw and how unfortunate i was at my unsuccessful attempt to record the orb. by the time i made a complete circle and reached tuscanny again, which was at about 8:16pm or so and still on the phone with my friend, i looked up and was searching for the orb again. after i walked about 50 yards on tuscanny from e. greenleaf dr., i saw it again or maybe even a different one. this time it was much further away and was traveling to my right and was pulsating from bright to not being visible back to bright again. i didnt attempt to film it this time because it was just to far away and i didnt believe my phone could have captured anything because of it being so far away. i observed its flight path and it pulsating in and out of a visible spectrum for about 10-15 seconds before it completely vanished from my sight. i stood there looking for about five minutes but it never appeared again. i couldnt stand there and wait to see if it would appear again like i wanted to because i had to finish my walk and get back to the pool to pick my daughter up.
content.summary: Went for a walk while my daughter was at swimming pratice. minutes into walk i saw the orb when i reached the end of the street.

content.detailedDescription:
Went out to my car and looked up to the nw and saw five large circles of light. 4 whitish/tinge of gold.  one blue-green (seemed to be the one in charge and was one the end.)  they were not in a line, but semi-line, could tell they were traveling together and at the same speed.  like when one sees a flock of birds traveling.  they were large, each one about the size of two cars put together.  they were completely silent.  very beautiful to look at.  past close over head, about distance a helicopter usually flies. they seemed transparent, with light inside the circles.  it wasn't like they had lights on them, but rather they were lights.  the light was contained in the circles.  i ran quickly back into the house to tell my family there were ufos.  they came out to front yard...Within those few seconds the objects had picked up speed and were in the distance heading se.  my son saw them as well as my grandsons.  we watched them ascend until they looked like stars...Then they were gone.
this happened at dusk with light still in the sky.
content.summary: Looked up and saw 5 perfect round circles of light, 4 white and one blue-green. large and moved se

content.detailedDescription: I was returning in from walking my dog, when i noticed a bright orange glow in the sky appearing from the south. i first thought it was a meteor. it continued to travel from south to north. the color was unlike anything i have ever seen in the sky. no flashing wing lights just an orange glow with a faint halo around it. after observing for about 30 seconds looking for flashing lights or a change of color and not seeing that, i dragged the dog inside and yelled for my wife, she came outside and was able to observe it as it continued north, she had her phone and i took it handing her the dog and ran out to snap some pictures. i took about 4 pictures it was quit some distance at that point. i will post the best picture i have. not sure what this was but it was unlike anything i have ever seen.
content.summary: Witnessed what i first believed to be a meteor. it had a very orange glow halo like. it moved steady from south to north with no sound

content.detailedDescription:
My girlfriend and i observed a cigar-disc type object hovering to the north very low (400-500 ft up). it was silent and had very bright colors rotating around it. it made no noise at all and would tilt. i ran through golf course to get better video angle on my phone. it started moving south, and then hooked around an apartment building to southeast. as i saw it come from behind building in distance, it appeared to change into an orange energy ball before i lost sight of it.  (9:11pm video - approx. 3min 5 sec in, and 9:17pm video energy ball).

approximately an hour later i observed a black triangle with three flashing bright lights (1 red, 2 white although one of the white lights appeared green at some points).  it flew from the south west approx. 800-1000 feet up, and circled over my head.  my iphone camera got static twice, after circling twice it took off fast to north-north east. (10:04pm video - 2min 30 sec in)
content.summary: Observed disc/cigar object hovering low with bright light rotating around then took off around apartment building. hr later observed diff triangle craft circle overhead

content.detailedDescription:
I was outside taking pictures of orbs at night with a digital camera with a flash.

when i was taking pictures by the house, i viewed through the viewfinder when taking these pictures and also use the flash.

sometimes i just point and snap without looking through the viewfinder.

looking through the camera's viewfinder, i seen this rainbow thing in the air just what it looks like, i quickly tried to get picture of it and i did!  it took the camera about 2-3 seconds to reload the flash to take another picture and i was able to again.

what is this? 

it's not a spiderweb, bug or any object. i've taken pictures of those things - bugs, spiderwebs, dust many times. 

i had moved my position slightly before taking the second picture. you can still see it changed position from one picture to the next as it came right at me in a westerly direction.

you can see the very low height of it by the satellite dish it is first near and the exterior of the house and in the second shot it is lower, coming in the camera's direction.

thank you.
content.summary: What is this rainbow colored thing i caught on camera? could see it move with own eyes.

content.detailedDescription: I was sitting on my porch enjoying the breeze before bedtime. i noticed a bright light across the street too low to be a star. it's started floating back and forth over my neighbor's field and house. i watched it for almost 5 minutes before i started recording it. it flashed bright and seemed to disappear. the it came back again, floated over the farm again and flashed bright once more. then it disappeared. i stayed outside for about another hour to try and see if it came back and it never did. third time i've seen things like this. first time i was able to capture it on camera.
content.summary: Orb like light floating in my neighbors field across the street. it hovered and changed directions at least 7 times. would disappear and reappear at random.

content.detailedDescription: I didn't see any ufo but we were taken inside one.   i haven't had any hypnosis to recall what happened but i can tell you why i believe we were taken.   we went camping in a shack out at bostwick and my spouse was drinking beer and the kids were playing games.  it was just a one room house with 3 windows and 1 bunk bed. when you walk in you could see the stove and the beds were on the same wall as the door. one bed was regular height and there was another bed about three feet above the regular one. there was about 3 to 4 chairs there. the kids were playing games at the table and my spouse and i were sitting talking, i thought about my brother that had come there the day before when i noticed there was a bright light in front of the cabin.  i thought my brother came back so i went to the door to greet him i opened the door and saw a bright light and the next thing i remember was sitting straight up in bed. i heard a whirring noise and i remember being afraid but i don't know why. i ask my spouse "did you hear that? he was laying face down he said "yeah"  i asked him what did that sound like to you? he said "a space ship leaving"  i don't know how the kids and my spouse and i got into bed.  i don't remember.  as soon as he said that we both scrambled out of bed grabbed the kids left all our food and bedding and ran to the boat and hightailed it back to town.  the funny thing is we never talked about that for about ten years.
content.summary: My husband, myself, my 9 year old son, 5 year old son and one year old son were camping in bostwick inlet and we were abducted by a ufo

content.detailedDescription: This is a recount of my girlfriend's encounter this morning.  she wouldn't report it herself but told me i could if i wanted. not a bser. she works nights and was tired driving home. driving due south, at i-10 at 8:25am.  she was texting me while at red lights on her way home.  she said she saw ufo.  definitely not an airplane.  she was instantly (and groggily) pondering "what could that be? because it isn't an airplane."  we are very accustomed to seeing aircraft there as departure end of tucson intl traffic is a constant presence out that way.  she said it was a little higher than aircraft that you see leaving tia there.  i used to be a usaf aviator.  i think the traffic there is usually about 2500 agl. "it was faster than airplanes." it was "shiny or reflective and round like a ball."  heading due "east", "fast," "it got super bright and vanished."  "kinda freaked me out."  she had zero doubt it was not an airplane or anything she's every seen before.  "about a mile away."  "3 inches down from the top of my windshield"  which would probably be 30 degrees up.  at "about a mile away", that's a bit lower than 2500 agl.
content.summary: Not an airplane though in se departure end of tia - silver craft heading east fast brightened light a bright silver ball and disappreared
